<subSubSection pageId="72" pageNumber="73" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="72.[151,1437,151,717]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,620,645]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Etymology.</emphasis>
From the Latin adjective “ 
<emphasis box="[638,703,620,645]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">ochra</emphasis>
”, meaning pale yellow, and “ 
<emphasis box="[1038,1103,620,644]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">femur</emphasis>
”, meaning thigh, thus a noun in apposition.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
